{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"DeviceMotionEvent()","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/DeviceMotionEvent","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Device_orientation_events\">Device orientation events</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent\"><code>DeviceMotionEvent</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><em><code>DeviceMotionEvent()</code></em></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/acceleration\"><code>acceleration</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/accelerationIncludingGravity\"><code>accelerationIncludingGravity</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/interval\"><code>interval</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/rotationRate\"><code>rotationRate</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event\"><code>Event</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Device Orientation Events</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEventAcceleration\"><code>DeviceMotionEventAcceleration</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEventRotationRate\"><code>DeviceMotionEventRotationRate</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceOrientationEvent\"><code>DeviceOrientationEvent</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <strong><code>DeviceMotionEvent()</code></strong> constructor creates a new <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent\"><code>DeviceMotionEvent</code></a> object.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">new DeviceMotionEvent(type)\nnew DeviceMotionEvent(type, options)\n</pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"type\"><code>type</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      A string with the name of the event.\n      It is case-sensitive and browsers always set it to <code>devicemotion</code>.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"options\"><code>options</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>An object that, <em>in addition of the properties defined in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event/Event\" title=\"Event()\"><code>Event()</code></a></em>, can have the following properties:</p>\n    <dl>\n      <dt id=\"acceleration\"><code>acceleration</code></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEventAcceleration\"><code>DeviceMotionEventAcceleration</code></a> object giving the acceleration of the device on the three axis X, Y and Z.\n          Acceleration is expressed in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meter_per_second_squared\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">m/s²</a>.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n      <dt id=\"accelerationincludinggravity\"><code>accelerationIncludingGravity</code></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEventAcceleration\"><code>DeviceMotionEventAcceleration</code></a> object giving the acceleration of the device on the three axis X, Y and Z with the effect of gravity.\n          Acceleration is expressed in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meter_per_second_squared\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">m/s²</a>.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n      <dt id=\"rotationrate\"><code>rotationRate</code></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEventRotationRate\"><code>DeviceMotionEventRotationRate</code></a> object giving the rate of change of the device's orientation on the three orientation axis alpha, beta and gamma.\n          Rotation rate is express in degrees per seconds.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n      <dt id=\"interval\"><code>interval</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>A number representing the interval of time, in milliseconds, at which data is obtained from the device. It defaults to <code>0</code>.</p>\n      </dd>\n    </dl>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>A new <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent\"><code>DeviceMotionEvent</code></a> object.</p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/deviceorientation/#dom-devicemotionevent-devicemotionevent","title":"DeviceOrientation Event Specification"}],"query":"api.DeviceMotionEvent.DeviceMotionEvent"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.DeviceMotionEvent.DeviceMotionEvent","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/DeviceMotionEvent/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The DeviceMotionEvent() constructor creates a new DeviceMotionEvent object.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-13T05:21:27.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"DeviceMotionEvent.DeviceMotionEvent()","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"DeviceMotionEvent.DeviceMotionEvent()","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/devicemotionevent/devicemotionevent","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/devicemotionevent/devicemotionevent/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/da88b2f3a23b9d93f083003f13c06f9d96073f6a","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent","title":"DeviceMotionEvent"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/DeviceMotionEvent","title":"DeviceMotionEvent()"}],"pageTitle":"DeviceMotionEvent() - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}